sentences: Robert Terrance Barnett (born February 2, 1972, in Fairburn, Georgia), professionally known by his stage name T-Mo Goodie (or simply T-Mo), is an American rapper from Atlanta.
He released his first solo project 2 the Fullest on October 31, 2000, via Stronghouse Productions.
He earned his Bachelor of Science degree from Morris Brown College in Atlanta, Georgia.
